parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
and may not respond to braking. The accelerator pedal may stick or feel soft
and the vehicle may surge forward or backward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sticking accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration, loss of control, and accidents, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels soft or spongy
or requires repeated tapping to disengage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control failure can cause unintended acceleration, loss of control, and accidents, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control fails to disengage when the brakes are applied
causing the vehicle to continue accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause accidents, injuries, and even fatalities, especially when the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: brake pedal travels to the floor
grinding or screeching noise when applying brakes
